review_blob: Dark, thick and Malty. This is a great Winter beer. Im glad I was sitting in front of a cool fan when I drank this one.
White fluffy head with lasts for a while. Orange in color with nice hoppy smell. Not too strong and finishes pleasantly.
White head that disappears quickly. Amber color with lots of bubbles. Smells spicey with a fruity finish. Great Stuff. I could drink this any day. Very refreshing.
Nice white frothy head with sediment floating in the glass. Amber/orange color. Smells and tastes very hoppy and very bitter at the end. Pretty good stuff.
Pours black with no head. Chocolate and bread flavor with fruity aftertaste. Not too much alcohol flavor.
Chillin with my friend Marc. We went to Lennys to get some beer and grub. The Stone Cold was "Stone Cold." Best beer Ive had at Lennys. Full of flavor, citrus and spice.

I love this stuff. I drank this the first time I went to Milwaukee  with my friend Marc; and boy does it bring back the memories. Cola and slight smoky flavor. Rich dark brown color with very little head. Goes down easy. One to recommend to your friends.

Not as bad as I thought it might be considering the reviews I read. Interesting pale yellow/orange color with very little head. Full of carbonation. This doesnt taste like any malt liquor Ive ever had. Its full of fruity flavor with the taste of corn. NIce.
beer_name: Rogue Dads Little Helper Malt Liquor

review_blob: Dark red when held up to the light. Not much head, even on a hard pour. Nice and bitter on the back of the tongue. Tastes like grapefruit. Wonderful!
Dark pour with not much head. A little lace as you drink. Nice and thick feel with chocolate in the middle and lots of fruit at the end. GREAT!
750ML bottle. Its good. Dark and cloudy as can be with an effervescent head and lots of bubbles. Tastes very fruity but not very thick on the palette like would be expected.

You have to get a 40 oz. to make this count. Pale yellow color, with foamy head that expands at the pour. Full of alcohol, thick in the mouth and not much of a definite flavor. Put it in the freezer to get it nice and cold.

Bananas and Circus Peanuts! Nice thick frothy head. White and bubbley with nice lace running down the glass. Feels good in the mouth with nice and thick viscosity. I love it. Beautifully crafted reddish, amber color.

I have to be outside for this one. And it helps if I pull it out of a big ice bucket where its so cold you cant taste it. Thats Coors whole selling point anyway. I guess theyve been successful. Once I finished the first semester of my freshman year in collage I graduated from this mass-marketed brew. Only if its free and nothing else is available.

Bitter, Bitter, Bitter. Dark red in color with no head and a little lace. From beginning to end you can taste the hops with a push of alcohol toward the end. Smells very flowery and feels full in the mouth. Not something to drink every day, but one to share with friends who like extra hoppy IPAs.
This stuff tastes like old, stale, honey. Id rather have a nice chilled mead. Dont put me through the torture.
I could drink this stuff forever. Some malt, but not as much as some. Im tasting hops and caramel. Lots of alcohol, but in a good way. Nice fluffy head and a great brown color. WONDERFUL!

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: This stuff was suprisingly good for only being $3.99 for a six pack and the fact that its from a "Big Box" Wisconsin Brewery. Not that it was the best beer Ive ever had or anything, but its really drinkable. It actually tastes kinda good. It has a lot of the basic characteristics of a good Belgian Dopplebock, but theyre on the weak side. Not a bad buy. Ill have to share the rest with my friends just so they can say theyve tried it.

Its hard to beat Old Rasputin. Full flavor with lots of coffee and malt. It pours out black and has a nice thick feel in your mouth. I like to drink this when my wife gives me a haircut. This should be served in every barber shop.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: One of the better Dopple Bocks Ive had. Pretty Malty with a thick head. Goes down smooth and subtle alcohol up front. Dark body.

I love this stuff. My favorite place to drink this is at the Rathskeller when Polka Boy is playing. 
Its smooth on the palate, high in alcohol and well balanced all the way through. It not the best Double Bock Ive had, but its one of the tops.
Nice thick head and dark in color. Full of malt, carmel and bread flavor.

Smelled sweet right at first pour. Amber in color. Tasted smooth with a nice alcohol feel and flavor, quite a bit of carbonation too. Some beers like this remind me a little of soy sauce. Thats not a bad thing. I would buy this again in a heartbeat. GOOD STUFF!
